\n\nSigns of an allergic reaction, like rash; hives; itching; red, swollen, blistered, or peeling skin with or without fever; wheezing; tightness in the chest or throat; trouble breathing, swallowing, or talking; unusual hoarsen', 'Data not available', 'Do not refrigerate. Do not freeze. Store below 30?C.', 'Nasal Decongestants & Other Nasal Preparations', 'Non-RX', 4, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Brompheniramine + Phenylephrine ', 'Dimetapp (Syrup)', 'Pfizer, Inc.', 'Pfizer, Inc.', 'Cough and Colds', 'Per 5 mL Brompheniramine maleate 2 mg, phenylephrine HCl 5 mg', 'Temporary relieves symptoms of cold, flu, and allergies including watery eyes, runny nose, sneezing and nasal congestion.', 'Dimetapp is a combination medicine used to treat symptoms caused by the common cold, flu, allergies, hay fever (allergic rhinitis) or other respiratory conditions such as sinusitis, bronchitis manage. Dimetapp contains a cough suppressant, a decongestant and an antihistamine.', 'Hypersensitivity to Dimetapp Syrup is a contraindication. In addition, Dimetapp Syrup should not be used if you have allergic, asthma attack, breast-feeding, narrow-angle glaucoma, stomach ulcer, and unable to urinate.', 'Symptoms of overdose may include: nausea, vomiting, loss of appetite, sweating, stomach/abdominal pain, extreme tiredness, agitation, confusion, flushing, hallucinations, yellowing eyes/skin, dark urine, seizures.', 'Hypersensitivity to Dimetapp Syrup is a contraindication. In addition, Dimetapp Syrup should not be used if you have allergic, asthma attack, breast-feeding, narrow-angle glaucoma, stomach ulcer, and unable to urinate.', 'Caution use in pregnancy and lactation, and in patients with certain medical conditions such as breathing problems, hypertension, enlarged prostate, diabetes, glaucoma,severe lung disease, or problems with the heart, kidney, or thyroid.', 'Drowsiness, vomiting, nausea, dry mouth or other allergic reactions.', 'Drug interactions may change how your medications work or increase your risk for serious side effects. This document does not contain all possible drug interactions. Keep a list of all the products you use (including prescription/nonprescription drugs and herbal products) and share it with your doctor and pharmacist. Do not start, stop, or change the dosage of any medicines without your doctor\'s approval.\n\nTaking certain MAO inhibitors with this medication may cause a serious (possibly fatal) dr', 'Store at room temperature away from light and moisture.', 'Nasal Decongestants', 'Non-RX', 3, 'True', 'Generic');
