('Butamirate citrate', 'Saphmirate-T50 (Tablet)', 'Sapphire Life Sciences PVT. LTD', 'Sapphire Life Sciences PVT. LTD', 'Cough and Colds', 'Butamirate Citrate', 'Symptomatic treatment of acute cough of any origin. Used for cough sedation before and after operation.', 'Symptomatic treatment of acute cough of any origin. Used for cough sedation before and after operation.', 'Swallow the tablet whole. Adults: 2 to 3 tablets 2 to 3 times daily. Adolescent >12 years:1 to 2 tablets daily.', 'If someone suspects an overdose of Saphmirate-T50 tablets or any medication, immediate action is vital. Contact emergency services or go to the nearest hospital without delay. Provide accurate details about the medication, including its name, dosage, and ingestion time, to assist healthcare professionals in their response. Do not attempt to treat the overdose at home, such as inducing vomiting, without professional guidance. Monitor the affected person\'s vital signs while awaiting medical assist', 'Please consult your doctor, pharmacist, or the product packaging for this information.', 'Please consult your doctor, pharmacist, or the product packaging for this information.', 'The following are the possible side effects that may arise from medications containing Butamirate Citrate. This is not an exhaustive list. The effects are possible, but they may not always occur. Some of the effects can be rare but potentially severe. Consult your doctor if you observe any side effects like dizziness, vomiting, diarrhea, and skin rash.\n\nIf you notice any additional side effects not listed above, contact your doctor for medical advice. You can also report them to your local food ', 'Data not available', 'Do not store above 25?C. Throw away the syrup 6 months after first opening the bottle.', 'Cough Suppressants', 'Non-RX', 4, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Butamirate citrate', 'Sinecod Forte (SR Tablet)', 'GLAXOSMITHKLINE CONSUMER HEALTHCARE PHILIPPINES INC.', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Cough and Colds', 'Butamirate citrate', 'Symptomatic treatment of acute cough of any origin. Used for cough sedation before and after operation. Available as sustained-release tablet.\nPlease read patient information leaflet for complete product information before use.', 'Symptomatic treatment of cough of various origins.', 'For adults, the recommended dosage is 2-3 tablets to be taken daily, with intervals of either every 8 or 12 hours. Adolescents aged over 12 years are advised to take 1 or 2 tablets daily. It\'s essential to swallow the tablet whole and not chew or crush it, and to follow with a sufficient amount of liquid. Adhering to these instructions ensures the appropriate and effective use of the medication for both adults and adolescents.', 'In the event of a suspected overdose of Sinecod Forte SR tablets or any medication, immediate action is essential. Contact emergency services or visit the nearest hospital promptly. Provide detailed information about the medication, including its name, dosage, and ingestion time, to assist healthcare professionals in their response. Avoid attempting self-treatment, such as inducing vomiting, without professional guidance. While awaiting medical help, monitor the affected person\'s vital signs and', 'This product should not be used by patients with known allergy to butamirate or to any of its components.', 'Caution use in pregnancy and lactation. Avoid concomitant use with other cough expectorants. May impair ability to drive or operate machinery.', 'Rarely dizziness, nausea, diarrhea & skin rash.', 'Data not available', '', 'Cough Suppressants', 'Non-RX', 9, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Camphor + Menthol ', 'Vicks (Inhaler)', 'P&G Health', 'Zuellig Pharma', 'Cough and Colds', 'Menthol, camphor', 'Helps clear stuffy nose due to colds.', 'Vicks Inhaler clears stuffy nose due to colds.', 'Adults and children 12 years of age and over 2 inhalations in each nostril. Children 6 to under 12 years (with adult supervision): 1 inhalation in each nostril. Children 2 to 6 years: Ask a doctor. Children under 2 years: Do not use.', 'Overdose with butamirate (Sinecod) may cause the following symptoms: somnolence, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, dizziness and low blood pressure.\nTreatment: Further management should be as clinically indicated or as recommended by the national poison centers, where available. There is no specific treatment for an overdose of butamirate. If overdose occurs, the patient should be treated supportively with appropriate monitoring as necessary. If the patient takes more Butamirate Citrate (Sinecod Forte', 'Hypersensitivity to Vicks Inhaler is a contraindication. In addition, Vicks Inhaler should not be used if you have Abdominal cramps, Flushing, Headache, Hypersensitivity, Nausea, Seizures, Tetracycline hydrochloride therapy, Vomiting, and children who hav', 'Before using Vicks Inhaler, inform your doctor about your current list of medications, over the counter products (e.g. vitamins, herbal supplements, etc.), allergies, pre-existing diseases, and current health conditions (e.g. pregnancy, upcoming surgery, etc.). Some health conditions may make you more susceptible to the side-effects of the drug. Like blood dyscrasias, Breastfeeding, Candidiasis, darkening of tongue, pregnancy, pregnant, planning to become pregnant or breastfeeding, skin erythema', 'The following is a list of possible side-effects that may occur from all constituting ingredients of Vicks Inhaler. This is not a comprehensive list. These side-effects are possible, but do not always occur. Some of the side-effects may be rare but serious. Consult your doctor if you observe any side-effects like Severe allergic rejection, Nausea, Vomiting, Ataxia, Abdominal pain, Drowsiness, Contact dermatitis, and Condition of involuntary eye movement.', 'Avoid taking simultaneously other cough medicines, because it may lead to accumulation of bronchial secretions in your lungs. Tell the doctor or pharmacist before use if patient is taking, or have recently taken, any regular medication on prescription or over-the-counter products.', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Other nasal preparation for topical use', 'Non-RX', 3, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Carbocisteine ', 'Ceascol (Syrup)', 'New Myrex Lab. Inc.', 'New Myrex Lab. Inc.', 'Cough and Colds', 'Carbocisteine ', 'Used for the treatment of disorders of the respiratory tract associated with excessive mucus. Indicated for chronic and acute bronchitis, pneumonia, pulmonary emphysema and bronchial asthma.\nEach 5 mL syrup contains 250 mg carbocisteine.', 'Ceascol Syrup is used for Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, Bronchiectasis and other conditions. Ceascol Syrup may also be used for purposes not listed in this medication guide.', 'For adults, the recommended initial dosage is 2.25 g per day, divided into multiple doses. As the condition improves, the dosage can be adjusted to 1.5 g daily, also divided into doses. For children, the recommended dosages are children aged 2 to 5 years: 62.5-125 mg taken four times daily. And children aged 6 to 12 years: 250 mg taken twice a day. Adhering to these prescribed dosages is vital to ensure the effective and safe administration of the medication for both adults and children.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Ceascol Syrup, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same condition or', 'Hypersensitivity to Ceascol Syrup is a contraindication. In addition, Ceascol Syrup should not be used if you have Active peptic ulceration, Adolescents, Allergic to it or any of its ingredients, and Children.', 'Before using Ceascol Syrup, inform your doctor about your current list of medications, over the counter products (e.g. vitamins, herbal supplements, etc.), allergies, pre-existing diseases, and current health conditions (e.g. pregnancy, upcoming surgery, etc.). Some health conditions may make you more susceptible to the side-effects of the drug. Take as directed by your doctor or follow the direction printed on the product insert. Dosage is based on your condition. Tell your doctor if your condi', 'The following is a list of possible side-effects that may occur from all constituting ingredients of Ceascol Syrup. This is not a comprehensive list. These side-effects are possible, but do not always occur. Some of the side-effects may be rare but serious. Consult your doctor if you observe any side-effects like difficulty in breathing, Allergic reactions, Swelling of face, Wheezing, Skin rash, Gastrointestinal bleeding, Ceascol Syrup may also cause side-effects not listed here.\nIf you notice o', 'Using Ceascol Syrup with certain drugs like aminoglycosides, colistin, ethacrynic acid, or furosemide can alter its effects and potentially lead to side effects or reduced effectiveness. Inform your doctor about all medications, vitamins, and herbal supplements you\'re taking to avoid or manage potential drug interactions.', 'Store medicines at room temperature, away from heat and direct light. Do not freeze medicines unless required by package insert. Keep medicines away from children and pets.\nDo not flush medications down the toilet or pour them into drainage unless instructed to do so. Medication discarded in this manner may contaminate the environment. Please consult your pharmacist or doctor for more details on how to safely discard Ceascol Syrup.', 'Mucolytic', 'Non-RX', 9, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Carbocisteine ', 'Solmux (Capsule)', 'UNILAB, Inc', 'UNILAB, Inc', 'Cough and Colds', 'Carbocisteine', 'Solmux Capsule is used for the treatment, control, prevention, & improvement of the following diseases, conditions and symptoms like Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, Bronchiectasis, and Solmux Capsule may also be used for purposes not listed here.', 'Carbocisteine (Solmux) is a mucolytic agent used to relieve cough characterized by excessive or sticky sputum or phlegm to help treat respiratory tract disorders such as acute bronchitis. Carbocisteine also reduces the number of exacerbations associated with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) and inhibits the adherence of bacteria and virus to human respiratory cells. Carbocisteine is also used in the treatment of otitis media with effusion (glue ear).', 'Adults & Children above 12 yrs. old: Take 1 capsule every 8 hours, or as recommended by the doctor.', 'Symptoms: Carbocisteine overdose is usually associated with stomach or intestinal discomfort.\nManagement: If the patient has taken more than the recommended dosage, consult a doctor or contact a poison control center right away.', 'This product should not be given to patients with active stomach or intestinal ulcer and those with allergy to carbocisteine or to any of its ingredients.', 'Caution use in patients with history of gastric or duodenal ulcer and gastrointestinal bleeding. If pregnant or breastfeeding, consult a doctor before taking any medication.', 'Stomach discomforts, nausea, diarrhea, headache, dizziness, and dry mouth.', 'Patients should always tell their doctor if they are taking other medicines, including herbal medicines and food supplements.', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Mucolytic', 'Non-RX', 6, 'True', 'Generic'),
