('Data not available', 'Bactidol Extra Soothing Lozenges 8\'s', 'Johnson & Johnson (Phils.) Inc.', 'Johnson & Johnson (Phils.) Inc.', 'Eyes, Ear, Nose, Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Hexetidine', 'These lozenges, with 8 per pack, aid in alleviating mouth and throat infections and contain Dichlorobenzyl alcohol at 1.2 mg and Amylmetacresol at 600 mcg.', 'For symptomatic treatment of acute sore throat.\nFor symptomatic treatment of acute and chronic pharyngitis, catarrh (irritation or inflammation) of the upper respiratory tract, and relief of unpleasant post-operative sensation in the throat.\nProvides flavourful and convenient relief from SORE THROAT.', 'The daily recommended dose is 1 lozenge every 2 to 3 hours with a maximum daily dose of 8 lozenges. Dissolve 1 lozenge slowly in the mouth. Do not chew or swallow the lozenge whole. Not to be administered for children below 6 years of age. Patient must seek medical attention immediately at the first sign of any adverse drug reaction.', 'Data not available', 'Data not available', 'Before using this product, tell your doctor or pharmacist if you are allergic to menthol; or if you have any other allergies. This product may contain inactive ingredients, which can cause allergic reactions or other problems. Talk to your pharmacist for more details.', 'A very serious allergic reaction to this drug is rare. However, get medical help right away if you notice any symptoms of a serious allergic reaction, including rash, itching/swelling (especially of the face/tongue/throat), severe dizziness, trouble breathing.', 'Data not available', ' Store at temperatures not exceeding 30oC.', 'Throat Lozenge medication', 'Non-RX', 1, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Benzydamine + Cetylpuridinium chloride ', 'Difflam (Lozenge)', 'iNova Pharmaceuticals (Phils.), Inc.', 'iNova Pharmaceuticals (Phils.), Inc.', 'Eyes, Ear, Nose, Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Each lozenge contains 3 mg of benzydamine hydrochloride (equivalent to 2.68 mg benzydamine). The other ingredients are isomalt (E 953), acesulfame potassium, citric acid monohydrate, orange flavour, honey flavour, levomenthol, quinoline yellow (E 104), sunset yellow (E 110).', 'These sugar-free lozenges are used to relieve pain associated with inflammatory conditions in the mouth and throat, including tonsillitis, pharyngitis, oral ulceration, and post-dental operations. Each lozenge contains 3 mg of Benzydamine hydrochloride and 1.33 mg of Cetylpyridinium chloride.', 'For the temporary relief of painful conditions of the oral cavity including tonsilitis sore throat, radiation mucositis, aphthous ulcers, post-orosurgical and periodontal procedures, pharyngitis, swelling and inflammatory conditions.', 'Slowly dissolve 1 lozenge in the mouth every 1-2 hours. Maximum of 12 lozenges daily to be taken for not more than 7 days. Do not give to children below 6 years old.', 'This medicine contains 31g isomalt per 12 lozenges (recommended maximum daily dose). Excess consumption of products containing isomalt may have a laxative effect. Please seek your doctor\'s advice if you have liver or kidney problems, pregnant or breastfeeding.', 'This product should not be used by patients with known allergy or hypersensitivity to any of its components.', 'May cause diarrhea or laxative effect in excessive consumption.', 'Stinging/ burning sensation in the mouth; Rarely hypersensitivity reactions.', 'Data not available', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C. Solution: Store below 30?C. Protect from light. Shelf-Life: 3 years.', 'Local Analgesic/ Anti-inflammatory', 'Non-RX', 6, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Benzydamine HCl', 'Difflam Forte (Throat Spray)', 'iNova Pharmaceuticals (Phils.), Inc.', 'iNova Pharmaceuticals (Phils.), Inc.', 'Eyes, Ear, Nose, Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Benzydamine hydrochloride.', 'This medication is employed to alleviate painful conditions in the mouth and throat, such as sore throat, tonsillitis, pharyngitis, and other inflammatory conditions, and it contains Benzydamine HCl at a concentration of 3 mg/mL.', 'Temporary relief of painful conditions of the oral cavity including: Tonsillitis, sore throat, pharyngitis, mouth ulcers eg, aphthous ulcer, radiation mucositis, post-orosurgical and periodontal procedures, swelling, redness and inflammatory conditions.\nChlorhexidine in Difflam-C helps reduce the development of plaque and gingivitis during the period of treatment when the usual oral hygiene measures are interrupted.', 'For adults, the recommended usage involves spraying the product 2 to 4 times directly onto the sore or inflamed area and swallowing gently. This process should be repeated every 1.5 to 3 hours as needed. Similarly, for children aged 6 to 12, the procedure is to spray the product 2 times onto the sore or inflamed area, followed by gentle swallowing. This regimen is advised to be repeated every 1.5 to 3 hours as necessary. Adhering to these guidelines ensures proper and effective relief for both a', 'There are no known cases of overdosage with Difflam lozenges and throat spray. Adverse central nervous system (CNS) effects have been reported following overdosage with high doses of Difflam solution. Difflam is unlikely to cause adverse systemic effects, even if accidental ingestion should occur.\nThere is no specific antidote for benzydamine and should excessive quantities be ingested, the treatment should be symptomatic. Excess consumption of products containing isomalt may have a laxative eff', 'Difflam Anti-inflammatory Throat Spray oral rinse is not suitable for use in children under 12 years. The spray can be used in children at a dose of up to 1 puff per 4kg of body weight (under 6) or 4 puffs (6-12 years) every 1.5 - 3 hours.', 'Before using Difflam Forte Anti-Inflammatory Throat Spray, inform your doctor about your current list of medications, over the counter products (e.g. vitamins, herbal supplements, etc.), allergies, pre-existing diseases, and current health conditions (e.g. pregnancy, upcoming surgery, etc.). Some health conditions may make you more susceptible to the side-effects of the drug. Take as directed by your doctor or follow the direction printed on the product insert. Dosage is based on your condition.', 'Difflam Forte Anti-Inflammatory Throat Spray is generally well-tolerated and side effects are minor. The most commonly reported reaction is oral numbness (2.6% of treated cases). Occasional burning or stinging sensation may occur (1.4%).', 'There are no known drug interactions with benzydamine.', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Nonsteroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs)', 'Non-RX', 4, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Benzydamine hydrochloride ', 'Difflam (Mint Lozenge)', 'iNova Pharmaceuticals (Phils.), Inc.', 'iNova Pharmaceuticals (Phils.), Inc.', 'Eyes, Ear, Nose, Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Benzydamine hydrochloride.', 'These sugar-free lozenges provide relief from pain associated with inflammatory conditions in the mouth and throat, such as tonsillitis, pharyngitis, oral ulceration, and post-dental operations, with each lozenge containing 3 mg of Benzydamine hydrochloride.', 'Temporary relief of painful conditions of the oral cavity including: Tonsillitis, sore throat, pharyngitis, mouth ulcers eg, aphthous ulcer, radiation mucositis, post-orosurgical and periodontal procedures, swelling, redness and inflammatory conditions.\nChlorhexidine in Difflam-C helps reduce the development of plaque and gingivitis during the period of treatment when the usual oral hygiene measures are interrupted.', 'Adults and children 6 years and over: 1 lozenge every 1 to 2 hours as required; maximum of 12 lozenges per day.', 'There are no known cases of overdosage with Difflam lozenges and throat spray. Adverse central nervous system (CNS) effects have been reported following overdosage with high doses of Difflam solution. Difflam is unlikely to cause adverse systemic effects, even if accidental ingestion should occur.\nThere is no specific antidote for benzydamine and should excessive quantities be ingested, the treatment should be symptomatic. Excess consumption of products containing isomalt may have a laxative eff', 'Hypersensitivity to Difflam Lozenge is a contraindication. In addition, Difflam Lozenge should not be taken if you have the following conditions like hypersensitivity.', 'Before using this medication, tell your doctor about your current list of medications, over the counter products (eg vitamins, herbal supplements, etc.), allergies, current illnesses, and current conditions. of health (eg pregnancy, upcoming surgeries, etc.). Some health conditions may cause you to have side-effects from the medication. Take as directed by a doctor or follow the directions printed on the product insert. Dosage is based on your condition. Like pregnant, planning to become pregnan', 'The following are possible side-effects from the ingredients of Difflam Lozenge. This is not a complete list. Side effects are possible, but not always. Some of the side effects may be rare but potentially serious. Consult your doctor if you observe any side-effects like rash, Skin swelling or redness, Difficulty in breathing, Wheezing, and Numbness.\nIf you notice any additional side-effects not listed above, contact your doctor for medical advice. You can also report to your local food and drug', 'There are no known drug interactions with benzydamine.', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Local Analgesic/ Anti-inflammatory', 'Non-RX', 4, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Dequadin ', '(Lozenge)', 'iNova', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Eyes, Ear, Nose, Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Dequalinium Cl', 'This medication is utilized to treat mouth and throat infections like oral thrush, pharyngitis, and tonsillitis, with each lozenge containing 250 mcg of dequalinium chloride.', 'For symptomatic relief of sore throat.', 'Adults: Dissolve slowly 1 lozenge in the mouth every 2-3 hours. Maximum dose of 8 lozenges per day.', 'Overdosage should not present a problem other than gastrointestinal discomfort.', 'Dequadin Lozenge should not be used by individuals with hypersensitivity to the product or any of its components, and it should also be avoided by those with a sensitivity or allergy to any substance.', 'Do not exceed recommended dosage.', 'The following are possible side-effects from the ingredients of Dequadin Lozenge. This is not a complete list. Side effects are possible, but not always. Some of the side effects may be rare but potentially serious. Consult your doctor if you observe any side-effects like vaginal discharge, and Itchiness.\nIf you notice any additional side-effects not listed above, contact your doctor for medical advice. You can also report to your local food and drug administration authority.', 'No clinically significant drug interactions known. it is not considered to constitute a hazard. No adverse effects known. Occasional hypersensitivity reactions and soreness of the tongue are possible.', 'Store medicines at room temperature, away from heat and direct light. Do not freeze medicines unless required by package insert.', 'Local Antiseptic', 'Non-RX', 6, 'True', 'Generic'),
