('Data not available', 'Kamillosan M (Throat Spray)', 'A. Menarini Philippines, Inc.', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Eyes, Ear, Nose, Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Chamomile and natural oil extracts.', 'This product is indicated for various oral and throat conditions, including inflammatory issues, gum problems, post-tooth extraction pain, mucosal irritation from dental appliances, tonsillar angina, canker sores, and bad breath, and it contains a combination of ingredients such as anise oil, bergamot oil, chamomile extract, cineol, methyl salicylate, peppermint oil, dwarf pine needle oil, and sage oil.', 'Inflammatory infection of the buccal and pharyngeal cavity, parodontosis, acute gingivitis, pain after tooth extraction and during 2nd dentition, mucosal irritation caused by dental plates, tonsillary angina, canker sores and bad breath.', 'Spray 3 times a day to the affected region of the buccal and pharyngeal cavity. 2 puffs applied with the spraying head correspond to a fully effective single dose. It is recommended to use the sprayer after meals.', 'Data not available', 'Hypersensitivity.', 'Do not spray directly to the nose. Contains about 25% ethyl alcohol by volume.', 'Symptoms of an occasional allergic reaction such as itching, rash, swelling, dizziness, breathing problem may occur, which may (rarely) cause angioedema and anaphylaxis. If patient feel any side effects, contact to doctor promptly.\n\nSafety during breast feeding or pregnancy has not been accounted. Individuals with a history of allergies to Asteracea or ragweed r plants such as sunflowers, daisies, chrysanthe?mums should not use Chamomile (Kamillosan Mouth Spray) supplements.', 'Data not available', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Mucolytic/ Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Non-RX', 7, 'True', 'Generic'),
