('Povidone-Iodine ', 'Betadine Gargle 1%', 'Mundipharma Distribution GmbH', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Eyes, Ear, Nose, Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Povidone-iodine.', 'Prevention and treatment of painful mouth and throat infections or swelling. Use as oral antiseptic before and after dental procedures.', 'Oral germicide for fast and soothing relief of sore throat and mouth sores. Breath freshener, where excessive bacteria in the mouth is present. Mouthwash for oral hygiene of postoperative or bedridden patients. Oral antiseptic before and after dental operations or tooth extractions. Ideal degerming soak for dentures and toothbrushes.', 'For the treatment of sore throat and mouth infections, gargle with 20 mL of undiluted solution for 30 seconds, 2-4 times daily or as required. Alternatively, for regular protection or as a mouthwash, use 20 mL of full-strength solution or dilute it with 20 mL of water and gargle for 30 seconds, repeating as necessary.', 'Signs & Symptoms: In the unlikely event to experience any of the following symptoms: stomach pain, unable to pass urine, loss of appetite, weakness, nausea and vomiting, coughing up blood, excessive sweating, difficulty in breathing, metabolic acidosis, anxiety and pale skin, immediately consult the doctor.\nTreatment is symptomatic and supportive.', 'This product should not be used by patients with known allergy or hypersensitivity to any of its components. Not indicated for patients with hyperthyroidism and children below 3 years old.', 'For external use only. If symptoms persist, consult your doctor. Not recommended during pregnancy.', 'Discontinue use in case of local irritation or hypersensitivity.', 'Do not apply other medications to the same affected areas treated with POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE), unless the doctor has told so.\nIt is not likely that other drugs the patient takes orally or inject will have an effect on externally applied POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE).\nThe concomitant use of other externally applied wound healing medicines/preparations may alter the effect of POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE). Products containing enzymatic component, alkali, mercury, silver, hydrogen peroxide, tannic ac', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.\nPaint: Discard when preparation is no longer golden-brown.', 'Local Antiseptic', 'Non-RX', 3, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Povidone-Iodine ', 'Betadine (Throat Spray)', 'Mundipharma Distribution GmbH', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Eyes, Ear, Nose, Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Povidone-iodine.', 'This throat spray is indicated for the treatment of acute mucosal infections of the mouth and pharynx including stomatitis, gingivitis, aphthous ulcers, pharyngitis, tonsillitis, monilial infections, common colds and influenza. For oral hygiene prior to, during and after dental and oral surgery. For fast and soothing relief of sore throat.\n', 'POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE) throat spray is indicated for the treatment of acute mucosal infections of the mouth and pharynx including stomatitis, gingivitis, aphthous ulcers, pharyngitis, tonsillitis, monilial infections, common colds and influenza.\nFor oral hygiene prior to, during and after dental and oral surgery.\nFor fast and soothing relief of sore throat.', 'Spray to the mucous membrane of the throat several times a day (every 3-4 hr).', 'Signs & Symptoms: In the unlikely event to experience any of the following symptoms: stomach pain, unable to pass urine, loss of appetite, weakness, nausea and vomiting, coughing up blood, excessive sweating, difficulty in breathing, metabolic acidosis, anxiety and pale skin, immediately consult the doctor.\nTreatment is symptomatic and supportive.', 'Do not use Betadine Sore Throat Gargle if you are allergic to povidone or any of the ingredients listed at the end of this leaflet.Always check the ingredients to make sure you can use this medicine. You have a severe sore throat accompanied by fever, hea', 'WARNINGS: Small amounts may be swallowed. If accidentally swallowed in large amounts, contact your healthcare professional or hospital immediately. Do not use if you are allergic to any ingredient, have any type of thyroid disorder, if you are pregnant or breast-feeding, or are using hydrogen peroxide.', 'WARNING/CAUTION: Even though it may be rare, some people may have very bad and sometimes deadly side effects when taking a drug. Tell your doctor or get medical help right away if you have any of the following signs or symptoms that may be related to a very bad side effect:\n\nSigns of an allergic reaction, like rash; hives; itching; red, swollen, blistered, or peeling skin with or without fever; wheezing; tightness in the chest or throat; trouble breathing, swallowing, or talking; unusual hoarsen', 'Do not apply other medications to the same affected areas treated with POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE), unless the doctor has told so.\nIt is not likely that other drugs the patient takes orally or inject will have an effect on externally applied POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE).\nThe concomitant use of other externally applied wound healing medicines/preparations may alter the effect of POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE). Products containing enzymatic component, alkali, mercury, silver, hydrogen peroxide, tannic ac', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.\nPaint: Discard when preparation is no longer golden-brown.', 'Local Antiseptic', 'Non-RX', 8, 'True', 'Generic');
