t your doctor if you observe any side-effects like Nausea, Vomiting, Diarrhea, Muscular twitching, and Inflammation of the gastrointestinal tract.\nIf you notice other side-effects not listed above, contact your doctor for m', 'Drug interactions may change how your medications work or increase your risk for serious side effects.Do not start, stop, or change the dosage of any medicines without your doctor\'s approval.', 'Store at room temperature. Do not freeze. Protect from heat. Store in a dry place. Do not store in a bathroom.', 'Other Nasal Preparations', 'Non-RX', 8, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Ambroxol ', 'Strepsils Chesty Cough (Lozenge)', 'Reckitt Benckiser Healthcare Philippines', 'Reckitt Benckiser Healthcare Philippines', 'Eyes, Ear, Nose, Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Ambroxol HCl.', 'These lozenges are designed to provide relief from productive or wet cough accompanied by sticky phlegm, typically associated with mild to moderate respiratory diseases, and each lozenge contains 15 mg of Ambroxol HCl.', 'Treatment of respiratory disorder associated with viscous mucus.', 'The recommended dosing regimen for this medication is as follows:\nFor adults, dissolve 2 lozenges consecutively in the mouth, repeating this process 3 times a day. As for children aged 5 to 10 years, dissolve 1 lozenge in the mouth 3 times a day, or as instructed by a medical professional. Adhering to these recommended dosages ensures effective management and relief of symptoms for both adults and children.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Strepsils Chesty Cough Lozenge, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the ', 'This product should not be given to patients with known hypersensitivity or allergy to any of its components.', 'Before using Strepsils Chesty Cough Lozenge, inform your doctor about your current list of medications, over the counter products (e.g. vitamins, herbal supplements, etc.), allergies, pre-existing diseases, and current health conditions (e.g. pregnancy, upcoming surgery, etc.). Some health conditions may make you more susceptible to the side-effects of the drug. Take as directed by your doctor or follow the direction printed on the product insert. Dosage is based on your condition. Like avoid us', 'The following is a list of possible side-effects that may occur from all constituting ingredients of Strepsils Chesty Cough Lozenge. This is not a comprehensive list. These side-effects are possible, but do not always occur. Some of the side-effects may be rare but serious. Consult your doctor if you observe any side-effects like Gastric ulceration, Strepsils Chesty Cough Lozenge may also cause side-effects not listed here.\n\nIf you notice other side-effects not listed above, contact your doctor ', 'Please consult your physician or pharmacist or product package for this information.', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Mucolytic/ Mouth & Throat Preparations', 'Non-RX', 8, 'True', 'Generic'),
