('Paracetamol ', 'Biogic (Tablet)', 'Azarias Pharmaceutical Laboratories, Inc.', 'Azarias Pharmaceutical Laboratories, Inc.', 'Fever and Pain Relief', 'Paracetamol', 'For the relief of minor aches and pains such as headache, backache, menstrua cramps, muscular aches, minor arthritis pain, toothache, and pain associated with common cold and flu.\nFor fever reduction.', 'Biogic Suspension is used to relieve mild to moderate pain from a headache, toothache, cold, flu, joint pain, or periods pain. This medicine works by reducing the activity of certain chemicals in the body to provide pain-relieving effects. Biogic is also used to reduce fever. This medicine reduces fever by increasing the loss of heat from the body.', 'Adults & children above 12 yrs. old: Take 1-2 tablets every 4 to 6 hours as needed. Do not take more than 4 g (8 tablets) per 24-hour period.', 'If you have taken more than the recommended dose of Biogic, get medical advice immediately. If the overdose has happened within the last 1 hour, the toxic effect can be reduced by taking activated charcoal. Activated Charcoal is a form of carbon that has small, low-volume pores. These pores help trap chemicals as in the case of poisoning. N-acetylcysteine may be used as an antidote up to 24 hours after overdose of Biogic. It is best to use N-acetylcysteine within 8 hours of overdose. Oral methio', 'Do not give to patients with allergy to paracetamol or any ingredient in the product. Not intended for long-term use in patients with anemia or with heart, lung, kidney, or liver disease.', 'Do not exceed recommended dosage. May cause liver damage in excessive amount or prolonged use. Do not use with other products containing paracetamol. Ask the doctor before use if patient has kidney or liver problems or if currently taking anticoagulants or blood-thinning medications. Discontinue use and consult the doctor if new symptoms occur or if condition worsens, if redness or swelling is present, if pain gets worse or lasts more than 5 days, and if fever gets worse or lasts more than 3 day', 'May cause skin rashes, hypersensitivity reactions, changes in number of white blood cells and platelets, and minor stomach and intestinal disturbances.', 'When two or more medicines are taken together, it can change how the medicines work and increase the risk of side-effects. In medical terms, this is called as a Drug Interaction.\nThis page does not contain all the possible interactions of Biogic Suspension. Share a list of all medicines that you use with your doctor and pharmacist. Do not start, stop, or change the dose of any medicines without the approval of your doctor.', 'Follow storage instructions on the product package if available. Store Biogic Suspension at 20-25?C (68-77?F), away from heat, away from moisture, and away from light. Store this medicine away from children and pets.', 'Analgesic/ Antipyretic', 'Non-RX', 7, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Paracetamol ', 'Rapidol (Tablet)', 'Flamingo Pharmaceuticals Ltd.', 'Flamingo Pharmaceuticals Ltd.', 'Fever and Pain Relief', 'Paracetamol', 'Used in the symptomatic management of pain, fever, and other aches and pain associated with colds and flu such as toothache, headache, and sore throat.\n\nPlease read patient information leaflet for complete product information before use.', 'Rapidol Tablet is used to relieve mild to moderate pain from a headache, toothache, cold, flu, joint pain, or periods pain. This medicine works by reducing the activity of certain chemicals in the body to provide pain-relieving effects. Rapidol is also used to reduce fever. This medicine reduces fever by increasing the loss of heat from the body.', 'For adults, the recommended dosage is 1-2 tablets every 4-6 hours, with a maximum of 8 tablets within a 24-hour period. Children aged 6-12 years should be given half to 1 tablet (250-500 mg) 3-4 times daily as needed. It\'s important not to exceed 10 days for pain or 3 days for fever, and if symptoms persist, consult a doctor.', 'If you have taken more than the recommended dose of Rapidol, get medical advice immediately. If the overdose has happened within the last 1 hour, the toxic effect can be reduced by taking activated charcoal. Activated Charcoal is a form of carbon that has small, low-volume pores. These pores help trap chemicals as in the case of poisoning. N-acetylcysteine may be used as an antidote up to 24 hours after overdose of Rapidol. It is best to use N-acetylcysteine within 8 hours of overdose. Oral meth', 'This product should not be given to patients with allergy to paracetamol (acetaminophen) or to any of its ingredients. Not intended for long-term use in patients with anemia, cardiac or pulmonary disease, and hepatic or severe renal disease. Do not give t', 'Do not exceed recommended dose. Caution use in patients with impaired kidney functions in patients taking liver medications. May cause liver damage in excessive amount or prolonged use. Avoid concomitant use with other products containing paracetamol. May interact with blood-thinning medications or anticoagulants.', 'Occasionally, skin rash and other allergic reactions; Anorexia, abdominal pain; Hematologic reactions including thrombocytopenia and agranulocytosis.', 'When two or more medicines are taken together, it can change how the medicines work and increase the risk of side-effects. In medical terms, this is called as a Drug Interaction.\nThis page does not contain all the possible interactions of Rapidol Tablet. Share a list of all medicines that you use with your doctor and pharmacist. Do not start, stop, or change the dose of any medicines without the approval of your doctor.', 'You should store Rapidol Tablet at 20-25?C (68-77?F), away from heat, away from moisture, and away from light. Store the medicine away from the reach of children and pets.', 'Analgesic/ Antipyretic', 'Non-RX', 8, 'True', 'Generic'),
