('Paracetamol + Ibuprofen ', 'I-laxx (Capsule)', 'Lumar Pharmaceutical Lab.', 'Lumar Pharmaceutical Lab.', 'Fever and Pain Relief', 'Paracetamol 325 mg, ibuprofen 200 mg', 'Used in the symptomatic relief of pain and fever, including headache, toothache, menstrual pain, migraine, post-operative pain, arthritis, spondylitis, sprains and strains, and mild to moderate pain in other musculoskeletal or joint disorders.\n\nEach capsule: Paracetamol 325 mg + Ibuprofen 200 mg\n\nPlease read patient information leaflet for complete product information before use.', 'I-Laxx Capsule is used for temporary relief of pain associated with a headache, backache, migraine, period pain, muscular pain, dental pain, sore throat, cold and flu symptoms, and fever. This medicine works by blocking the activity of a chemical in the brain that causes pain. I-Laxx Capsule is also used to reduce fever, and to reduce inflammation (redness, swelling, and soreness).', 'Take one capsule 3-4 times a day or as prescribed by a physician.', 'In the case of paracetamol poisoning, immediate medical treatment is given to overcome the risk of liver injury and emptying of the stomach (gastric lavage) should also be considered. For reversing the liver injury antidote therapy of acetylcysteine and methionine should be used as soon as possible. Acetylcysteine should be used within 8 hours of taking paracetamol overdose. Initially 150 mg/kg or 68.18 mg/lb of acetylcysteine in 200 ml 5% glucose is given through blood veins (intravenous or I. ', 'This product should not be given to patients with known hypersensitivity or allergy to paracetamol, ibuprofen, aspirin, and other nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs), those who had bronchospasm, angioedema, nasal polyps, or allergic-type reactio', 'Do not exceed recommended dose. Avoid concomitant use with products containing paracetamol, ibuprofen, or other nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs). Caution use in elderly, in patients with peptic ulcer, and disease of the liver, kidney, or heart. Long-term use may increase risk of stroke. Avoid or limit alcohol intake.', 'Gastrointestinal discomforts such as abdominal pain, diarrhea, flatulence; GI bleeding; dizziness, headache, skin rash, and other allergic or hypersensitivity reactions.', 'When two or more medicines are taken together, it can change how the medicines work and increase the risk of side-effects. In medical terms, this is called as a Drug Interaction.\nI-Laxx Capsule may interact with warfarin, which is used in the treatment of stroke. Ibuprofen may interfere with the bleeding time, increases the risk of severe and fatal bleeding in the stomach and intestinal tract. Dose reduction is recommended in patients using paracetamol with an anticoagulant for a longer time. Cl', 'You should store I-Laxx Capsule at below 30?C (86 ?F), and away from light. Store the medicine away from the reach of children and pets.', 'Nonsteroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drugs (NSAIDs)', 'Non-RX', 1, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Paracetamol + Ibuprofen ', 'Painaide', 'Azarias Pharmaceutical Laboratories, Inc.', 'Azarias Pharmaceutical Laboratories, Inc.', 'Fever and Pain Relief', 'Paracetamol 325 mg, ibuprofen 200 mg', 'Used in the symptomatic relief of pain and fever, including headache, toothache, menstrual pain, post-operative pain and mild to moderate pain in other musculoskeletal or joint disorders.\n\nEach capsule/tablet: Paracetamol 325 mg + Ibuprofen 200 mg\n\nPlease read patient information leaflet for complete product information before use.', 'Painaide Tablet is used for temporary relief of pain associated with a headache, backache, migraine, period pain, muscular pain, dental pain, sore throat, cold and flu symptoms, and fever. This medicine works by blocking the activity of a chemical in the brain that causes pain. Painaide is also used to reduce fever. It is also used to reduce inflammation (redness, swelling, and soreness).', 'For temporary relief of pain, adults aged 18 years and older can take 500 mg to 1000 mg of Paracetamol combined with 150 mg to 300 mg of Ibuprofen every 6 hours, with a maximum daily limit of 3000 mg of Paracetamol and 900 mg of Ibuprofen.', 'In the case of paracetamol poisoning, immediate medical treatment is given to overcome the risk of liver injury and emptying of the stomach (gastric lavage) should also be considered. For reversing the liver injury antidote therapy of acetylcysteine and methionine should be used as soon as possible. Acetylcysteine should be used within 8 hours of taking paracetamol overdose. Initially 150 mg/kg or 68.18 mg/lb of acetylcysteine in 200 ml 5% glucose is given through blood veins (intravenous or I. ', 'This product should not be given to patients with known hypersensitivity or allergy to paracetamol, ibuprofen, aspirin, and other nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs), those who had bronchospasm, angioedema, nasal polyps, or allergic-type reactio', 'Do not exceed recommended dose. Avoid concomitant use with products containing paracetamol, ibuprofen, or other nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs). Caution use in elderly, in patients with peptic ulcer, and disease of the liver, kidney, or heart. Long-term use may increase risk of stroke. Avoid or limit alcohol intake.', 'Nausea, vomiting, anorexia, diarrhea; dizziness, paresthesia, hallucinations; conjunctivitis, tinnitus; urticaria, toxic epidermal necrolysis; and fluid retention and palpitation.', 'When two or more medicines are taken together, it can change how the medicines work and increase the risk of side-effects. In medical terms, this is called as a Drug Interaction.\nPainaide Tablet interacts with antidepressants with anticholinergic properties, propantheline, cholestyramine, and narcotic analgesics, which are used to treat depression, excessive sweating, itching, and pain respectively. When paracetamol is used with antidepressants, propantheline, or with a narcotic analgesic, it ma', 'Store Painaide Tablet at below 30?C (86 ?F), and away from light. Keep this medicine away from children and pets.', 'Analgesic/ Antipyretic/ Anti-inflammatory', 'Non-RX', 3, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Paracetamol + Propyphenazone + Caffeine ', 'Saridon Triple Action (Tablet)', 'Bayer HealthCare Philippines, Inc.', 'Bayer HealthCare Philippines, Inc.', 'Fever and Pain Relief', 'Paracetamol 250 mg, propyphenazone 150 mg, caffeine 50 mg', 'For the relief of mild to severe headaches.\nEach tablet contains: Paracetamol 250 mg + Propyphenazone 150 mg + Caffeine 50 mg.\nPlease read patient information leaflet for complete product information before use.', 'For fast and effective relief of mild to severe headaches.\nFor the relief of pain such as headache, toothache, menstrual discomfort, postoperative and rheumatic pain.\nFor the relief of pain and fever associated with colds and \"flu\".', 'For a single dose, adults can take 1-2 tablets, while adolescents aged 12-16 years can take 1 tablet, with the option of repeating the dose up to three times within 24 hours if needed. It\'s important to take the tablets with plenty of water or another fluid and not to use them for more than one week or at doses exceeding the recommended amounts, unless directed by a doctor.', 'Signs and Symptoms of Overdose: Following overdose, symptoms of paracetamol poisoning often appear within 24-48 hours, but may be delayed beyond this time.\nSymptoms: Poisoning is more likely to occur in the presence of alcohol. Liver damage (hepatocellular necrosis) and impairment of liver function may occur and may progress to hepatic coma. Clinical indications of liver damage may not manifest until 2-4 days following overdose.\nHypokalemia and metabolic acidosis (including lactic acidosis) may ', 'This product should NOT be taken by patients with hypersensitivity or allergy to pyrazolones or related compounds, phenylbutazone-containing products, paracetamol, acetylsalicylic acid/ aspirin, caffeine, glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (G6PD) defiecien', 'Do not take more than the recommended dose. Caution use in patients with asthma, chronic rhinitis, urticaria, impaired hepatic and renal function, Gilbert?s syndrome, hematopoetic dysfunction. For pediatric patients and those taking other medications, consult your doctor.', 'Occasionally, allergic reactions such as skin rash, urticaria, pruritus, erythema angioedema, dyspnea, or asthma.', 'Hypnotics, Anti-epileptic drugs (phenobarbital, phenytoin, carbamazepine), Rifampicin, Propanthelin, Metoclopropamide, Chloramphenicol, Zidovudine, Barbiturates, Antihistaminics, Benzodiazepines, Oral contraceptives, Cimetidine, Disulfiram, Theophylline, Ephedrine, Smoking, Alcohol.', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 25?C.', 'Analgesic/ Antipyretic', 'Non-RX', 9, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Permethrin ', 'Kwell (Shampoo)', 'Aspen Phils.', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Hair and Scalp', 'Permethrin', 'Non-toxic shampoo used for the treatment and prevention of head lice & their eggs (kuto at lisa).\nEach mL contains 10 mg of Permethrin.', 'Treatment of head lice and their eggs and prevention for those at risk.', 'Wet hair, apply and lather enough Permethrin (Kwell) Shampoo to cover entire hair and scalp including areas behind the ears and nape. Leave for 10 minutes before rinsing the hair thoroughly with water. Towel dry.', 'Data not available', 'This product should not be used in patients with known allergy to pyrethrin or to any of its ingredients.', 'For external use only. Do not use on open scalp wounds. Avoid contact with eyes.', 'The following is a list of possible side-effects that may occur from all constituting ingredients of Kwell Shampoo. This is not a comprehensive list. These side-effects are possible, but do not always occur. Some of the side-effects may be rare but serious. Consult your doctor if you observe any side-effects Irritation, Difficulty in breathing, feeling of tightness in chest or throat, Itching on skin and Stinging or tingling.\nIf you notice other side-effects not listed above, contact your doctor', 'Data not available', 'Store below 30?C. Protect from light (shampoo).', 'Pediculicide', 'Non-RX', 5, 'True', 'Generic');
