('Diosmin + Hesperidin ', 'Daflon 500 (Tablet)', 'Servier Phils, Inc.', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Hemorrhoids', 'Daflon 500 Micronized purified flavonoid fraction 500 mg (equiv to diosmin 450 mg, hesperidin 50 mg). Daflon 1000 Micronized purified flavonoid fraction 1,000 mg (equiv to diosmin 900 mg, hesperidin 100 mg)', 'Treatment of venous insufficiency or disorders of the legs (venous leg ulcer) and hemorrhoidal attacks and diseases such as varicose veins, night cramps, edema, and hemorrhoids. Each film-coated tablet: Micronized purified flavonoid fraction 500 mg (MPFF, diosmin 450 mg and flavonoids as hesperidin 50 mg).\nPlease read patient information leaflet for complete product information before use.', 'Recommended for treating venous circulation disorders (swollen legs, pain, nocturnal cramps) and for treating symptoms due to acute hemorrhoidal attack.', 'The usual dosage for this medication is to take 1 tablet in the midday and 1 tablet at night. During an acute hemorrhoidal attack, it\'s recommended to take 3 tablets twice daily for the first 4 days, followed by 2 tablets twice daily for the next 3 days. Afterward, continue with 2 tablets daily, and all doses should be taken with meals, or as directed by your doctor.', 'Symptoms: There is limited experience with Daflon overdose. The most frequently reported adverse events in overdose cases were gastrointestinal events (such as diarrhea, nausea, abdominal pain) and skin events (such as pruritus, rash).\nManagement: Management of overdose should consist in treatment of clinical symptoms.\nIf the patient taken more Daflon than he/she should, contact the doctor or pharmacist immediately.', 'If you are allergic to diosmin or hesperidin or any other ingredients of Daflon 500mg tablet.', 'This medicine is not a substitute for a specific treatment of other anal disorders. Avoid long-term use. If the symptoms persist, consult your doctor. Breastfeeding is not recommended during the treatment period.', 'Mild stomach discomforts and neurovegetative disorders such as hypersomnia, fatigue, and increased appetite but did not require suspension or termination of treatment.', 'The patient must always tell the doctor or pharmacist about any other treatment the patient is receiving.\nNo interaction studies have been performed. No clinically relevant drug interaction has been reported to date from post marketing experience on the product.', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Antivaricose/ Antihemorrhoidal', 'Non-RX', 9, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Phospholipids ', 'Essentiale Forte P (Capsule)', 'A. NATTERMANN & CIE. GMBH', 'OPELLA HEALTHCARE PHIL INC', 'Liver Protectors', 'Phospholipids', 'Nutritional support for damaged liver due to toxins or diseases such as fatty liver and liver cirrhosis (complicated scarring of the liver).\nEach capsule: 300 mg of essential phospholipids (EPLs) from soya beans.', 'Nutritional support in the management of damaged liver (due to chronic liver disease, liver cirrhosis, fatty liver & intoxication by hepatotoxic substances).', 'ADULTS & CHILDREN above 12 yrs. old: Take 2 capsules 3 times a day, with meals and plenty of water.', 'No overdose reaction nor symptom of intoxication has been reported to date with Phospholipids (Essentiale Forte P) 300 mg hard gel capsule.\nThe monograph informs that the listed undesirable effects may be reinforced.\nThe patient should consult the doctor who may decide about the severity and any measures that might be necessary.', 'This product should not be given to patients with allergy to soya bean or to any of its ingredients.', 'Caution use in patients with chronic hepatitis. Not recommended for children below 12 yrs. old. Seek doctor\'s advice if pregnant or breastfeeding before using any medication or supplement.', 'Stomach discomforts, soft stool, and diarrhea.', 'An interaction of Phospholipids (Essentiale Forte P) 300 mg hard gel capsule with anticoagulants cannot be excluded. For this reason, dose adjustment of the anticoagulant might be necessary.\nConsult a doctor in the case of simultaneous application.', 'Store in the original container, not above 25?C.\nStore in the original container in order to protect from humidity.\nShelf life: 2 Years.', 'Liver Therapy', 'Non-RX', 8, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Meclizine HCl ', 'Bonamine (Chewtab)', 'Taisho Pharmaceutical Co. Ltd', 'Taisho Pharmaceutical Co. Ltd', 'Motion sickness & Vertigo', ' Meclizine Hydrochloride', 'For the prevention and treatment of nausea, dizziness and vomiting associated with motion sickness.', 'Bonamine Tablet is used for Nausea, Vomiting and dizziness caused by motion sickness, Symptoms of vertigo and other conditions.', 'For Bonamine Chewable Tablet for Kids 12.5 mg, children aged 11 and above should take 2 tablets, while those aged 5-10 should take 1 tablet one hour before travel for 24-hour protection. If an additional dose is required, it should be administered with a 4-hour interval, and children between 5-15 years old should not exceed two single doses.\n\nFor Bonamine Chewable Tablet for Adults 25 mg, for motion sickness, adults and children over 11 years old should take 1-2 tablets (25-50 mg) one hour befor', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Bonamine Tablet, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same condition ', 'This product should not be given to patients with known hypersensitivity or allergy to meclizine or to any of its components.', 'Caution is used in patients with glaucoma and enlarged prostate. May impair ability to drive or operate machinery. If pregnant or breastfeeding, seek doctor\'s advice before using this product.', 'Blurred vision, fatigue, dry mouth, and drowsiness. May cause excitability especially in children.', 'If you use other drugs or over the counter products at the same time, the effects of Bonamine Tablet may change. This may increase your risk for side-effects or cause your drug not to work properly. Tell your doctor about all the drugs, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are using, so that you doctor can help you prevent or manage drug interactions. Bonamine Tablet may interact with the following drugs and products: Alcohol', 'Store this medication at room temperature, protect it from light and moisture, and keep it out of the reach of children.', 'Antiemetic ', 'Non-RX', 3, 'True', 'Generic'),
