('Loperamide HCl ', 'Imodium (Capsule)', 'Johnson & Johnson (Phils.) Inc.', 'Johnson & Johnson (Phils.) Inc.', 'Stomach and intestinal disorders', 'Loperamide HCl', 'Used for the symptomatic relief of acute and chronic diarrhea. Helps control symptoms of diarrhea associated with bowel disorders.', 'Imodium Capsule is used for Loose stools, Mild travelers diarrhea, Non infective diarrhea, Idiopathic diarrhea in aids patients, Diarrhea, Loose bowel movements and other conditions.', 'For adults and children aged 12 years and above, initially take 2 capsules, followed by 1 capsule after each loose or watery stool, with a maximum of 8 capsules per day. Adjust the dose as needed until achieving 1-2 normal solid stools per day, and consult a doctor if symptoms persist.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Imodium Capsule, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same condition ', 'Do not give to patients with allergy to loperamide or to any ingredient in the product, to children below 12 years old, to pregnant or breastfeeding women, to patients with constipation or whom constipation should be avoided, and to those with swollen abd', 'Caution use in patients with hepatic dysfunction, dysentery, and those who should avoid constipation. Give oral replacement fluids as first line of treatment for dehydration due to diarrhea. Not recommended for use in children below 12 years old.', 'Dry mouth, abdominal pain, distention or discomfort, nausea, vomiting, flatulence, dyspepsia, and constipation. Rarely, drowsiness or dizziness and urinary retention.', 'When using Imodium Capsule, it\'s important to be aware that the concurrent use of other medications or over-the-counter products can potentially alter its effects, increasing the risk of side effects or reducing the drug\'s effectiveness. To ensure the safe and proper use of Imodium Capsule, it is crucial to inform your doctor about all the drugs, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently taking. Your doctor can then assist you in preventing or managing any potential drug interactions. N', 'Store medicines at room temperature, away from heat and direct light. Do not freeze medicines unless required by package insert. Keep medicines away from children and pets.', 'Antimotility/ Antidiarrheal', 'Non-RX', 1, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Loperamide HCl ', 'Lomotil (Tablet)', 'Johnson & Johnson (Phils.) Inc.', 'Johnson & Johnson (Phils.) Inc.', 'Stomach and intestinal disorders', ' Atropine Sulfate and Diphenoxylate Hcl ', 'Used along with electrolyte and fluid replacement for symptomatic relief of acute and chronic diarrhea. Helps control symptoms of diarrhea associated with bowel disorders.', 'Lomotil Tablet is used for Diadrrhea, Cramping, Diarrhea, Convulsion, Antidote for mushroom poisoning, Hypotonic radiography, Spasms and other conditions.', 'For adults and children above 12 years old, the usual dose is 1-6 tablets per day. In cases of acute diarrhea, start with 1-2 tablets initially, followed by 1 tablet after each loose or watery stool. For chronic diarrhea, begin with 1-2 tablets initially and adjust the dose until achieving 1-2 solid stools per day, with a maximum dose of 6 tablets per day.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Lomotil Tablet, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same condition o', 'This product should not be taken by individuals with allergy to loperamide or any of its ingredients, pregnant or breastfeeding women, constipated patients and also in people who should avoid constipation and patients with acute dysentery and active ulcer', 'Caution use in patients taking anti-infectives and other medications, and those with severe or persistent diarrhea and liver dysfunction. Not recommended for use in children below 12 yrs old.', 'Headache, feeling dizzy or drowsy, itchy skin or rash, stomach pain, nausea, or vomiting, dry skin or mouth, feeling restless, malaise (general feeling of weakness or discomfort), loss of appetite.', 'When taking Lomotil Tablet, it\'s crucial to be aware that combining it with other medications or over-the-counter products can potentially alter its effects, leading to an increased risk of side effects or reduced effectiveness. To ensure the safe and effective use of Lomotil Tablet, it\'s essential to inform your doctor about all the drugs, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently using. Your doctor can then provide guidance on preventing or managing any potential drug interactions. Lo', 'Store medicines at room temperature, away from heat and direct light. Do not freeze medicines unless required by package insert. Keep medicines away from children and pets.', 'Antimotility/ Antidiarrheal', 'Non-RX', 2, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Senna ', 'Senokot (Tablet)', 'Mundipharma Distribution GmbH', 'Mundipharma Distribution GmbH', 'Stomach and intestinal disorders', 'Per Senokot tab Ca sennosides 8.77 mg (equiv to 187 mg). Per Senokot Forte tab Ca sennosides 17.54 mg (equiv to 374 mg)', 'Used as natural laxative for the relief of constipation.', 'Used as a natural laxative for the relief of constipation.', 'For Senokot tablets with 187 mg of active ingredient, adults can take 2 tablets, with a maximum dose of 4 tablets twice a day. Children weighing more than 60 lbs. or 27.3 kg can be given 1 tablet, with a maximum dose of 2 tablets twice a day, preferably at bedtime or as directed by a doctor.\n\nFor Senokot Forte tablets with 374 mg of active ingredient, adults can take 1-2 tablets, with a maximum dose of 2 tablets twice a day, preferably at bedtime. The dose can be increased by 1 tablet up to the ', 'Signs & Symptoms: The major symptoms of overdose/abuse with any stimulant laxative including those containing senna are griping pain and severe diarrhea, leading to excessive water loss (dehydration) and possible electrolyte imbalance.\nTreatment should be supportive with generous amounts of fluid. Electrolytes, especially potassium, should be monitored. This is especially important in the elderly.\nIn case of accidental overdose, please consult the doctor.', 'This product should not be used when abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting or other symptoms of appendicitis are present.', 'Possibly unsafe when used for longer than 1 week or in doses above 34.4 mg sennosides twice daily. Long-term use can cause the bowels to stop functioning normally and might cause dependence on laxatives. Long-term use can also cause liver damage and other harmful effects.', 'May cause abdominal pain. Rarely, allergic reactions.', 'There are no known drug interactions with sennosides.', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Laxatives', 'Non-RX', 7, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Simethicone ', 'Restime (Chewtab)', 'UNILAB, Inc', 'UNILAB, Inc', 'Stomach and intestinal disorders', 'Simeticone', 'Relief of stomach discomfort due to gas accumulation including bloating, feeling of fullness, and dyspepsia.', 'This medicine is used to relieve discomfort due to the accumulation of gas in the stomach and intestines including sensations of bloating, pressure, fullness or stuffed feeling which can be caused by certain food (e.g., carbonated drinks, legumes, potatoes, infant formula, etc), air swallowing and dyspepsia.\nFor the relief of symptoms of excess gas associated with colic.', 'Children above 12 years old can chew 1-2 tablets, while those aged 2-12 years can chew 1 tablet. Tablets should be thoroughly chewed before swallowing, and all doses should be administered 4 times daily after meals and at bedtime, with a maximum daily dose of 500 mg or as prescribed by the doctor.', 'There have been no cases of overdosage reported with simeticone use. If overdosage is suspected, consult a doctor immediately.\nIf patient has taken more than the recommended dosage, consult a doctor.', 'This product should not be used by patients with hypersensitivity or allergy to simethicone or to any of its ingredients.', 'Avoid carbonated drinks and food that can increase stomach gas. Caution use in pregnancy and in patients with phenylketonuria. Ask doctor\'s advice if taking other medications like antacids or digestives before using this product.', 'There have been no reports of undesirable effects after ingestion of simeticone. A very severe allergic reaction is rare.', 'Reduce air swallowing by avoiding fizzy, carbonated drinks, and food that may increase gas in the stomach.', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Antiflatulent', 'Non-RX', 8, 'True', 'Generic');
