('Benzalkonium Cl + Cetrimide', 'Drapolene (Cream)', 'GlaxoSmithKline Philippines, Inc.', 'GlaxoSmithKline Philippines, Inc.', 'Topical products', 'Per g Benzalkonium Cl 100 mcg, cetrimide 2 mg', 'For the treatment of minor skin irritations such as diaper rash, redness, urinary dermatitis in adults, minor burns, and wounds.\nBenzalkonium chloride solution 0.02% w/w (benzalkonium chloride 0.01% w/w and cetrimide 0.2% w/w).', 'For the relief of diaper rash and for use as an adjunct to baby care hygiene for the prevention of diaper rash. For the relief of urinary dermatitis in adults, as an adjunct to patient care hygiene for the prevention of urinary dermatitis.', 'For nappy rash: Clean & dry affected area. Apply cream evenly after every diaper change, particularly to the folds of the skin.\nFor burns & wounds: Apply as directed.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Drapolene Cream, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same condition ', 'This product should not be used by patients with known hypersensitivity or allergy to any of its components.', 'For external use only', 'May cause skin irritation or itching; Rarely, allergic reaction.', 'When using Drapolene Cream, it\'s essential to be aware that the concurrent use of other medications or over-the-counter products can potentially alter its effects, leading to an increased risk of side effects or reduced efficacy. To ensure the safe and effective use of Drapolene Cream, it\'s crucial to inform your doctor about all the drugs, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently taking. Your healthcare provider can then provide guidance on how to prevent or manage any potential drug ', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Topical Antiseptic/ Disinfectant', 'Non-RX', 9, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Benzoic acid + Salicylic acid ', 'United Home Whitfield\'s (Ointment)', 'UNILAB, Inc', 'UNILAB, Inc', 'Topical products', 'Per g Salicylic acid 60 mg, benzoic acid 120 mg', 'Used for the treatment of superficial skin infections like ringworm especially during its chronic hyperkeratolytic stages. Can also be used in skin disorders characterized by skin itchiness and thickening.\nEach gram contains 120 mg of benzoic acid and 60 mg of salicylic acid.', 'For the treatment of athlete\'s foot (alipunga), ringworm (buni) and tinea versicolor (an-an).', 'Apply a generous amount of ointment on affected areas, once or twice daily, or as directed by the physician.', 'The use of large doses of topical salicylic acid may lead to salicylate intoxication and even death, particularly in children. (See Adverse Reactions.)\nHowever, when used as recommended, an overdose of topical salicylic acid + benzoic acid ointment is unlikely to occur.\nIf the patient has used more than the recommended dosage, or in case of accidental swallowing, consult a doctor.', 'This product should not be given to patients with known allergy to its active ingredients.', 'Keep out of reach of children. Avoid getting into the eyes.', 'Salicylic acid: Local irritation, skin inflammation, signs of salicylate toxicity (e.g., thirst, tinnitus or ringing in the ears, loss of hearing, headache, dizziness, vomiting, diarrhea, depression and disorientation) and allergic.', 'This medicine contains salicylic acid which may be absorbed and cause interactions with a number of other medicines. Tell the doctor if the patient is using the following medicines: Topical and oral salicylates (e.g., methyl salicylate-containing products, aspirin): May lead to salicylate toxicity.\nOther topical medicines (e.g., corticosteroids): Salicylic acid promotes shedding of the outermost skin layer which may increase the clinical effect of certain topical medicines by increasing drug pen', 'Keep container tightly closed.\nStore at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.\nDo not freeze.', 'Topical Antifungal', 'Non-RX', 9, 'True', 'Generic'),
