ment, it\'s essential to inform your doctor about your current medications, allergies, pre-existing conditions, and any upcoming surgery. Follow your doctor\'s directions or the product insert for dosage, and inform your doctor if your condition doesn\'t improve or worsens. Important points to consider include avoiding breathing dust and preventing contact with eyes, skin, and clothing.', 'Possible side effects of Dr. S Wong Bioderm Ointment, although not exhaustive, may include breathing difficulties, mouth swelling, tongue or lip rashes, hives, and skin redness or irritation at the application site. If any of these side effects persist or worsen, consult your doctor.', 'When using Bioderm Ointment, it\'s crucial to be aware that the effects of this medication can be influenced by the concurrent use of other drugs or over-the-counter products. This interaction can potentially increase the risk of side effects or reduce the effectiveness of Bioderm Ointment. To ensure the safe and proper use of this ointment, it\'s essential to inform your doctor about all the drugs, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently taking. Your healthcare provider can then offer ', 'Store medicines at room temperature, away from heat and direct light. Do not freeze medicines unless required by package insert. Keep medicines away from children and pets.', 'Local Anti-infective', 'Non-RX', 8, 'True', 'Generic'),
('', 'Calmoseptine (Ointment)', 'Calmoseptine Phils, Inc.', 'METRO DRUG INC', 'Topical products', 'Per 3.5 g Zn oxide 555.7 mg, calamine 164.5 mg, menthol, Na bicarbonate, phenol, lanolin, thymol, chlorothymol, glycerin', 'This ointment serves as a moisture barrier, providing relief and healing for various skin conditions, including diaper rash, burns, cuts, rashes, insect bites, irritation, acne, wounds, and more. It contains 555.7 mg of zinc oxide and 164.5 mg of calamine per 3.5 g sachet.', 'Protects, soothes and helps promote healing of impaired skin integrity related to: Feeding tube site leakage; wound drainage (to protect peri-wound skin from maceration) (peristomal and parastomal skin irritations); urinary and fecal incontinence, bedsores; ileoanal reservoirs, ileostomy, urostomy; moisture eg, perspiration; acne, scrapes; fungal infections, eczema, impetigo; diaper rash (children and adults); insect bites; burns (flame, radiation, chemical); fistula, fissures, excoriation; colo', 'Cleanse skin gently with mild skin cleanser. Allow to air dry. Apply a thin layer of ointment on the affected skin area 2 to 4 times daily.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Calmoseptine Ointment, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same cond', 'This product should not be used in patients with known hypersensitivity or allergy to any of its ingredients.', 'FOR EXTERNAL USE ONLY. Do not apply on deep or punctured wounds. Avoid contact with eyes. Keep out of children\'s reach. If condition worsens or does not improve within 7 days, consult your doctor.', 'Redness, warmth, or irritation at the application site may occur.', 'When using Calmoseptine Ointment, it\'s essential to be aware that the concurrent use of other drugs or over-the-counter products can potentially alter its effects. This interaction may heighten the risk of experiencing side effects or diminish the effectiveness of the ointment. To ensure the safe and appropriate use of Calmoseptine Ointment, it\'s imperative to inform your doctor about all the medications, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently taking. Your healthcare provider can pro', 'Store at a temperature not exceeding 30?C.\nShelf-Life: 3 years.', 'Skin Emollients & Protectants', 'Non-RX', 2, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Clotrimazole ', 'Canesten (Cream 1%)', 'Bayer HealthCare Philippines, Inc.', 'Bayer HealthCare Philippines, Inc.', 'Topical products', 'Clotrimazole', 'Used in the treatment of fungal infections such as white spots (An-an), ringworm (Buni), Athlete\'s foot (Alipunga), jock itch (Hadhad) and other skin fungal infections.', 'For the treatment of dermatomycoses caused by fungi, yeasts and molds: Athlete\'s foot (alipunga), Hand fungus, Ringworm (buni), Jock itch (hadhad), Pityriasis versicolor (an-an), Other skin fungal infections (cutaneous candidiasis, erythrasma).', 'Apply a thin layer on the affected area 2-3 times daily for 2-4 weeks to eliminate symptoms, thoroughly kill the fungus, and restore the healthy state of your skin or as prescribed by the doctor.', 'Signs and Symptoms of Overdose: No risk of acute intoxication is seen as it is unlikely to occur following a single dermal application of an overdose (application over a large area under conditions favorable to absorption) or inadvertent oral ingestion.\nWhen patient has taken more than the recommended dosage: There is no specific antidote however patients should still consult their physician.', 'This product should not be used in patients with known hypersensitivity or allergy to clotrimazole, other antifungal agents, or to any of its components.', 'For external application only. Avoid contact with eyes. Caution use in pregnancy and in children below 2 years old.', 'Rarely, skin reactions or local irritation.', 'None known.', 'Store below 30?C.', 'Topical Antifungal', 'Non-RX', 6, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Data not available', 'Efficascent (Oil)', 'International Pharmaceuticals, Inc.', 'International Pharmaceuticals, Inc.', 'Topical products', 'Camphor, Menthol and Methyl Salicylate', 'Efficascent Oil Regular variant, containing methyl salicylate, menthol, and camphor, is designed for massage and relaxation. It provides fast relief from various ailments, including back and muscular pains, cramps, rheumatism, arthritis, headaches, and more.', 'Efficascent Oil is used for Back pain, Muscle or joint pain, Anti-pain topical medication, Warts, Itching, Arthritis, Respiratory tract diseases, Bruising, Pain in muscle strains or sprains, Muscle strains and other conditions. ', 'Apply a liberal amount by gentle massage on the affected area until skin penetration is complete; repeat 3-4 times if necessary.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Efficascent Oil, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same condition ', 'Efficascent Oil should not be used by individuals who are hypersensitive to it or have conditions such as abdominal cramps, flushing, headache, hypersensitivity, or nausea.', 'Before using Efficascent Oil, it\'s important to inform your doctor about your current medications, allergies, pre-existing health conditions, and any ongoing health issues. This is especially crucial if you are pregnant, breastfeeding, have blood dyscrasias, or experience conditions like candidiasis or darkening of the tongue. Follow the recommended dosage and directions provided by your doctor or on the product label, and consult your doctor if your condition persists or worsens.', 'While using Effica