('Data not available', 'Efficascent (Ointment)', 'International Pharmaceuticals, Inc.', 'International Pharmaceuticals, Inc.', 'Topical products', 'Camphor, Menthol and Methyl Salicylate', 'Efficascent Ointment is an oil-based preparation of Efficascent Oil. \nIt is very effective in relieving pains, itches, cramps, and muscle discomforts such as stiff neck, lumbago, rheumatism, flatulence, minor sprains and strains, joint pains, and headache.', 'Efficascent Ointment is used for Anti-pain topical medication, Cold sores, Pain in arthritis, Pain in shoulder joint, Pain in tendons, Pain in muscle strains or sprains, Back pain, Bruising, Cramping, Muscle or joint pain and other conditions.', 'Swab a liberal amount of the ointment on your fingers then gently massage into the affected area.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Efficascent Ointment, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same condi', 'Efficascent Ointment should not be used if you have hypersensitivity to it or if you experience conditions such as abdominal cramps, flushing, or headaches.', 'Before using Efficascent Ointment, it\'s important to inform your doctor about your current medications, allergies, existing health conditions, and any ongoing health issues such as blood dyscrasias, breastfeeding, candidiasis, darkening of the tongue, or pregnancy, as these factors may affect its use. Follow your doctor\'s instructions or the directions on the product insert, and if your condition persists or worsens, consult your healthcare provider.', 'The following is a list of possible side-effects that may result from the components in Efficascent Ointment. These side-effects, including nausea, vomiting, ataxia, abdominal pain, drowsiness, and contact dermatitis, are not exhaustive and may not always manifest. If you experience any of these side-effects, particularly if they persist, it is advisable to consult your doctor.', 'When using Efficascent Oil, it\'s crucial to be aware that the concurrent use of other drugs or over-the-counter products can potentially impact its effects. This interaction might elevate the risk of experiencing side effects or compromise the efficacy of the oil. To ensure the safe and appropriate use of Efficascent Oil, it\'s essential to inform your doctor about all the medications, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently taking. Your healthcare provider can provide guidance on how ', 'Store medicines at room temperature, away from heat and direct light. Do not freeze medicines unless required by package insert. Keep medicines away from children and pets.', 'Topical Analgesics', 'Non-RX', 2, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Data not available', 'Efficascent (Relaxing Oil)', 'International Pharmaceuticals, Inc.', 'International Pharmaceuticals, Inc.', 'Topical products', 'Camphor, Menthol and Methyl Salicylate', 'Efficascent Relaxing Oil is the aromatherapeutic oil of your trusted liniment brand in a roll-on format which is very convenient and on-the-go. It helps relieve headache, travel & motion sickness, stomach/abdominal pain, dizziness, stiff neck, stuffy nose, itchiness, and insect bites.', 'Efficascent Oil is used for Back pain, Muscle or joint pain, Anti-pain topical medication, Warts, Itching, Arthritis, Respiratory tract diseases, Bruising, Pain in muscle strains or sprains, Muscle strains and other conditions. ', 'Rub gently into forehead and other intended ares. Apply as necessary.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Efficascent Relaxing Oil, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same c', 'Hypersensitivity. Childn <2 yrs. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Avoid contact with mouth, eyes and mucous menbrane. Keep away from children.', 'Severe burning, stinging, irritation. Rash, breathing difficulty, swelling of face, lips, tongue, throat.', 'When using Efficascent Oil, it\'s crucial to be aware that the concurrent use of other drugs or over-the-counter products can potentially impact its effects. This interaction might elevate the risk of experiencing side effects or compromise the efficacy of the oil. To ensure the safe and appropriate use of Efficascent Oil, it\'s essential to inform your doctor about all the medications, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently taking. Your healthcare provider can provide guidance on how ', 'Store medicines at room temperature, away from heat and direct light. Do not freeze medicines unless required by package insert. Keep medicines away from children and pets.', 'Topical Analgesics', 'Non-RX', 7, 'True', 'Generic'),
