('Ketoconazole ', 'Nizoral (Cream 2%)', 'Johnson & Johnson (Phils.) Inc.', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Topical products', 'Ketoconazole', 'Used in the treatment of common skin fungal infections including athlete\'s foot, jock itch, and tinea or ringworm infections.\nPer gram cream contains 20 mg ketoconazole.\nPlease read patient information leaflet for complete product information before use.', 'Ketoconazole (Nizoral) 2% Cream is indicated for topical application in the treatment of dermatophyte infections of the skin: tinea corporis, tinea cruris, tinea manus and tinea pedis due to Trichophyton rubrum, Trichophyton mentagrophytes, Microsporum canis and Epidermophyton floccosum, as well as in the treatment of cutaneous candidosis and tinea (pityriasis) versicolor.\nKetoconazole (Nizoral) 2% Cream is also indicated for the treatment of seborrheic dermatitis, a skin condition associated wi', 'Apply small amount on the affected area(s) and massage cream until it is evenly distributed. Use once daily for 2-4 weeks depending on the type or severity of skin fungal infection.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Nizoral Cream, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same condition or', 'This product should not be given to patients with known hypersensitivity or allergy to any of its components.', 'Before using ketoconazole, tell your doctor or pharmacist if you are allergic to it; or to other azole antifungals such as clotrimazole, econazole, or miconazole; or if you have any other allergies.', 'Local skin irritation or burning sensation; Rarely allergic reactions.', 'When using Nizoral Cream, it\'s vital to be aware that its effects can be influenced by other drugs or over-the-counter products, potentially leading to an increased risk of side effects or reduced effectiveness. To ensure the safe and proper use of this medication, it is crucial to inform your healthcare provider about all the drugs, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently taking. Your doctor can provide guidance on how to prevent or manage any potential drug interactions. Nizoral Cre', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Topical Antifungal', 'Non-RX', 8, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Menthol + Methyl salicylate + Eucalyptus oil', 'White Flower ', 'Hoe Hin Pak Fah Yeow Mfy. Ltd. Hong Kong', 'Hoe Hin Pak Fah Yeow Mfy. Ltd. Hong Kong', 'Topical products', 'Camphor 6% Menthol 15% Methyl salicylate 40%', 'Used to relieve headache, dizziness, stress, motion sickness, muscle pain, insect bites, common colds and stuffy nose and gives soothing aromatherapy.', 'White Flower Embrocation Solution is used for Itching, Arthritis, Smooth muscle relaxant in upper gastrointestinal endoscopy, Minor mouth or throat irritation, Muscle cramps, Muscle sprains, Headaches, Anti-pain topical medication, Muscle or joint pain, Muscle strains and other conditions. ', 'Adults and children 3 years of age and older: Apply a few drops then gently rub into the affected area not more than 4 times daily.\nFor younger children, consult your doctor.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of White Flower Embrocation Solution, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have t', 'White Flower Ointment is contraindicated if you have hypersensitivity to it, as well as in cases of abdominal cramps, flushing, headache, nausea, and with neonates.', 'Before using White Flower Ointment, it\'s essential to inform your doctor about your current medications, allergies, pre-existing diseases, and health conditions. Follow the provided directions and inform your doctor if your condition persists or worsens. Additionally, avoid alcohol consumption and be cautious if you have blood dyscrasias, are breastfeeding, or experience candidiasis or darkening of the tongue.', 'Possible side-effects of White Flower Ointment may include nausea, vomiting, ataxia, abdominal pain, drowsiness, and contact dermatitis. Consult your doctor if you experience any of these side-effects, especially if they persist.', 'When using White Flower Embrocation Solution, it\'s important to be aware that its effects may be altered when used concurrently with other drugs or over-the-counter products. Such interactions could potentially increase the risk of side effects or hinder the effectiveness of the medication. To ensure the safe and proper use of this solution, it is essential to inform your healthcare provider about all the drugs, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently taking. Your doctor can provide g', 'Other information - keep container tightly closed - store at 15? to 30?C (59? to 86?F)', 'External analgesic', 'Non-RX', 10, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Methyl salicylate + Menthol + Camphor ', 'Katinko (Ointment)', 'Greenstone Pharmaceutical H.K. Inc.', 'Greenstone Pharmaceutical H.K. Inc.', 'Topical products', ' Camphor Topical, Eucalyptus Oil Topical, Menthol Topical and Methyl Salicylate Topical ', 'Helps relieve minor pains and itch, muscle strain, neck and shoulder stiffness, sprain, back pain, headache, colds, travel sickness, bruises, flatulence, insect bite, and minor skin irritations.', 'Katinko Ointment is used for Pain, Warts, Cold sores, Hemorrhoids, Osteoarthritis, Gum diseases, Plaques, Bleeding gums, Delayed onset muscle soreness, Musculoskeletal aches and pains and other conditions.', 'Apply the ointment to affected areas in adults and children aged 2 years and older, but consult a doctor before using it on children under 2 years of age.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Katinko Ointment, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same condition', 'Katinko Ointment is contraindicated if you have hypersensitivity to it, as well as in the presence of abdominal cramps, flushing, headache, or nausea.', 'Before using Katinko Ointment, it\'s essential to inform your doctor about your current medications, allergies, pre-existing health conditions, and any ongoing health issues, as certain conditions like blood dyscrasias, breastfeeding, candidiasis, darkening of the tongue, and pregnancy may affect its use. Follow your doctor\'s instructions and the product insert for proper dosage and guidance. If your condition persists or worsens, consult your doctor.', 'Possible side effects of Katinko Ointment may include a mild cold or burning sensation at the application site, severe allergic reactions, nausea, vomiting, ataxia, and abdominal pain. If any of these side effects persist or worsen, consult your doctor for guidance.', 'Please consult your physician or pharmacist or product package for this information.', 'Store medicines at room temperature, away from heat and direct light. Do not freeze medicines unless required by package insert. Keep medicines away from children and pets.', 'Topical Counterirritant', 'Non-RX', 7, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Mometasone furoate', 'Elica (0.1%)', 'BAYER PHILIPPINES, INC', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Topical products', 'Mometasone furoate', 'Used to help stop itching, reduce redness and ease swelling due to eczema and other manifestations of atopic dermatitis and psoriasis.', 'Relief of the inflammatory and pruritic manifestations of corticosteroid responsive dermatoses eg, psoriasis and atopic dermatitis.\nElica lotion may be applied to scalp lesions.', 'Apply thin player on the affected area once a day. Do not use for more than 2 weeks, unless prescribed by the doctor.', 'Symptoms: Excessive, prolonged use of topical corticosteroids can suppress pituitary-adrenal function resulting in secondary adrenal insufficiency.\nTreatment: Appropriate symptomatic treatment is indicated. Acute hypercorticoid symptoms are virtually reversible. Treat electrolyte imbalance, if necessary. In cases of chronic toxicity, slow withdrawal of corticosteroids is advised.', 'This product should not be used in patients with known hypersensitivity or allergy to corticosteroids or to any of its components.', 'For external use only. Avoid contact with eyes. Caution use in pregnancy and lactation. Avoid prolonged use in infants and children.', 'Stinging, tingling, or burning sensation. Discontinue use if any allergic reaction or irritation occurs.', 'Please consult your physician or pharmacist or product package for this information.', 'Store at temperature not exceeding 30?C.', 'Topical Corticosteroid/ Anti-inflammatory', 'Non-RX', 1, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Data not available', 'Omega Pain Killer', 'Interhealthcare Pharmaceuticals, Inc.', 'Interhealthcare Pharmaceuticals, Inc.', 'Topical products', 'Methyl salicylate + Menthol + Camphor', 'A liniment preparation specially formulated for fast relief of back and muscular pains from overwork, cramps, rheumatism, lumbago, arthritis, stiff neck, headache, gas pain, insect bites, minor burns and bruises, sprains, and skin irritations.', 'Omega Pain Killer Liniment Oil is used for Back pain, Pain, Joint pain, Muscle or joint pain, Muscle pain, Anti-pain topical medication, Asthma, Cough, Pain in shoulder joint, Fungal infections of toenail and other conditions.', 'Shake well before using.Adults and children 3 years of age and older: Apply to affected area not more than 3 to 4 times daily.Children under 3 years of age: Consult a physician.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Omega Pain Killer Liniment Oil, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the ', 'Omega Pain Killer Liniment Oil should not be used if you are hypersensitive to it or have conditions such as abdominal cramps, flushing, headache, nausea, or if you are a neonate.', 'Before using Omega Pain Killer Liniment Oil, inform your doctor about your current medications, allergies, pre-existing conditions, and follow the recommended dosage. Avoid alcohol consumption and be cautious if you have conditions like blood dyscrasias, breastfeeding, candidiasis, or experience darkening of the tongue.', 'Possible side-effects of Omega Pain Killer Liniment Oil include skin vasodilation, abdominal pain, mild cold or burning sensation at the application site, severe allergic reactions, increased heart rate, slower breathing, and reduced appetite. Consult your doctor if you experience these symptoms, especially if they persist.', 'When using Omega Pain Killer Liniment Oil, it\'s crucial to be aware that its effects can be influenced by the concurrent use of other drugs or over-the-counter products. This can potentially elevate the risk of experiencing side effects or diminish the efficacy of the medication. To ensure the safe and effective use of this liniment oil, it\'s essential to inform your healthcare provider about all the drugs, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently taking. Your doctor can offer guidance', 'Store medicines at room temperature, away from heat and direct light. Do not freeze medicines unless required by package insert. Keep medicines away from children and pets.', 'Topical Analgesic', 'Non-RX', 5, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Data not available', 'Salonpas Medicated Patch', 'Hisamitsu', 'Hisamitsu', 'Topical products', 'Menthol, Methyl Salicylate and Tocopheryl Acetate', 'Use for relief of aches, pains and inflammations associated with:\nmuscle fatigue, muscle pain, stiff shoulder, simple backache, bruises, sprains, strains, arthritis, bone fracture, minor frostbite.', 'Salonpas Patch is used for Back pain, Anti-pain topical medication, Muscle or joint pain, Muscle strains, Arthritis, Bruising, Pain in arthritis, Pain in shoulder joint, Pain in tendons, Pain in muscle strains or sprains and other conditions. ', 'For adults and children aged 12 and above, clean and dry the affected area, then apply the patch not more than 3-4 times daily. Consult a doctor before use for children under 12 years old.', 'Do not use more than prescribed dose. Taking more medication will not improve your symptoms; rather they may cause poisoning or serious side-effects. If you suspect that you or anyone else who may have overdosed of Salonpas Patch, please go to the emergency department of the closest hospital or nursing home. Bring a medicine box, container, or label with you to help doctors with necessary information.\nDo not give your medicines to other people even if you know that they have the same condition o', 'Salonpas is not recommended for individuals who have recently undergone or are planning to have heart surgery, have a history of stomach bleeding, suffer from high blood pressure, heart disease, kidney disease, take diuretics, are pregnant, breastfeeding,', 'Do not use on wounds or damaged skins and if allergic to aspirin or salicylates.\nDiscontinue use & consult doctor, if symptoms persist for more than 7 days, if condition cleared up then occured again within few days, and if rash, itching or excessive skin irritation occurs.', 'A very serious allergic reaction to this drug is rare. However, get medical help right away if you notice any symptoms of a serious allergic reaction, including: rash, itching/swelling (especially of the face/tongue/throat), severe dizziness, trouble breathing. This is not a complete list of possible side effects.', 'When using Salonpas Patch, it\'s essential to be aware that its effects can be affected by the concurrent use of other drugs or over-the-counter products. This can potentially heighten the risk of experiencing side effects or diminish the medication\'s efficacy. To ensure the safe and effective use of this patch, it\'s crucial to inform your healthcare provider about all the drugs, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are currently taking. Your doctor can provide guidance on how to prevent or manag', 'Store medicines at room temperature, away from heat and direct light. Do not freeze medicines unless required by package insert. Keep medicines away from children and pets.', 'Topical Analgesic', 'Non-RX', 1, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Data not available', 'Vicks VapoRub', 'Procter & Gamble Distributing (Phils.) Inc.', 'Procter & Gamble Distributing (Phils.) Inc.', 'Topical products', 'Camphor + Eucalyptus Oil + Menthol', 'Cold vaporising ointment for the temporary relief of nasal congestion, cough, and other symptoms of common colds.', 'Vicks Vaporub Ointment is used to treat Bronchitis sinusitis, Swelling, Respiratory infections, Pain, Itching, Fungal infection of the fingernails, Warts, Cold sores, Hemorrhoids, Osteoarthritis, Respiratory tract pain, and other conditions.', 'For relief, massage VICKS VAPORUB on throat, chest and back.\nFor use in steam: Partly fill a bowl with steaming water, add 2 teaspoonfuls of VapoRub and inhale vapours for 10-15 minutes. Repeat as necessary. Children should be closely supervised to avoid scalding.\nWhen using this product, do not apply heat or heat/reheat (using microwave/stove), add to boiling water or container where water is being heated. Failure to follow these instructions can cause hot product to splatter and burn the face ', 'Do not take more than prescribed to you. Taking more medication will not improve your condition; instead, it may lead to poisoning or severe side effects. If you believe that you or someone you know has taken an overdose of Vicks Vaporub Ointment, immediately go to the nearest hospital or clinic. Bring the medicine box, container, or label to make it easier for doctors to get the necessary information.\nDo not give your medicine to other people, even if you know they have the same condition or se', 'Hypersensitivity to Vicks Vaporub Vaporizing Ointment is a contraindication, and it should not be used if the individual has a history of hypersensitivity or seizures.', 'Before using Vicks Vaporub Vaporizing Ointment, it\'s important to inform your doctor about your current medications, including over-the-counter products, any allergies you may have, pre-existing medical conditions, and your current health status, especially if you are pregnant, planning to become pregnant, or breastfeeding. It\'s crucial to follow your doctor\'s or product insert\'s directions for use, and the dosage should be based on your specific condition. Importantly, do not take this ointment', 'Possible side effects of Vicks Vaporub Vaporizing Ointment may include nausea, vomiting, ataxia, abdominal pain, drowsiness, contact dermatitis, and involuntary eye movement. Consult your doctor if any of these side effects persist or worsen.', 'If you are taking other medications or over-the-counter products simultaneously, the effects of Vicks Vaporub Ointment may change. This could increase the likelihood of experiencing side effects or result in the medicine not working correctly. Inform your doctor about all the medications, vitamins, and herbal supplements you are taking so that your doctor can prevent any potential interactions or make necessary adjustments. Vicks Vaporub Ointment may interact with the following products: Alcohol', 'Store Below 30?C.', 'other nasal preparations for topical use.', 'NP', 8, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Orlistat ', 'Xenical (Capsule)', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Weight management', 'Orlistat', 'Used in the treatment of obesity, along with low calorie intake or proper diet, exercise, and healthy lifestyle.', 'Orlistat (Xenical), in conjunction with a mildly hypocaloric diet, is indicated for treatment of obese patients or overweight patients with associated comorbidities.', 'Adults: Take 1 capsule 3 times a day, immediately before, during, or up to 1 hour after a meal.', 'Single doses of 800 mg Orlistat (Xenical) and multiple doses of up to 400 mg t.i.d. for 15 days have been studied in normal-weight and obese subjects without significant adverse findings. In addition, doses of 240 mg t.i.d. have been administered to obese patients for 6 months without significant increase of adverse findings.\nOrlistat overdose cases received during post-marketing reported either no adverse events or adverse events that are similar to those reported with recommended dose.\nShould ', 'This product should not be given to patients with known allergy to orlistat or to any of its components. Patients taking immunosuppressants like cyclosporine and those with chronic malabsorption syndrome or cholestasis should not take this product. Not re', 'Caution use in individuals below 18 yrs old and those who have had organ transplant, or other health conditions such as diabetes. Long-term use may require intake of fat-soluble vitamins to be taken at least 2 hours before or after orlistat dose.', 'Fatty stools, rectal pain or discomfort, bloating, tiredness, tooth or gum problem, and fecal incontinence.', 'Decreases in the absorption of vitamin D, E and ?-carotene have been observed when co-administered with Orlistat (Xenical). If a multivitamin supplement is recommended, it should be taken at least two hours after the administration of Orlistat (Xenical) or at bedtime.\nA reduction in cyclosporin plasma levels has been observed when Orlistat (Xenical) is co-administered (see General under Precautions). Therefore it is recommended to monitor more frequently than usual the cyclosporin plasma levels ', 'Do not store above 25?C. Store in original package and keep the blister in the outer carton, in order to protect from light and moisture.', 'Anti-Obesity', 'Non-RX', 9, 'True', 'Generic'),
('povidone iodine', 'Betadine (Cream/Ointment)', 'Mundipharma Distribution GmbH', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Wound care', 'Povidone-iodine', 'Prevention and treatment of common skin infections caused by minor injuries, cuts, wounds, abrasions, scrapes, burns, and lacerations; Used as topical antiseptic before and after surgery.', 'Cream: POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE) cream is an ideal topical agent for prevention of infection in burns, lacerations, cuts and abrasions; treatment of common skin infections, and for infection control during circumcision, suture removal and dressing changes.\nPOVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE) cream may be used for degerming care of stasis ulcers, decubitus ulcers and the umbilical area and in other procedures where degerming is needed.\nOintment: POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE) ointment is an ideal topical age', 'Clean & dry the affected skin. Apply liberally. May be covered w/ a dressing or bandage. May be used as often as required. Cream Burns 8 hrly. Other treatments Apply once daily.', 'Signs & Symptoms: In the unlikely event that the patient experiences any of the following symptoms: stomach pain, unable to pass urine, loss of appetite, weakness, nausea and vomiting, coughing up blood, excessive sweating, difficulty in breathing, metabolic acidosis, anxiety and pale skin, immediately consult the doctor.\nTreatment is symptomatic and supportive.', 'Hypersensitivity. Hyperthyroidism or any thyroid diseases. Patients on lithium therapy. Before & after a specific medical treatment involving the use of radioactive iodine.', 'Avoid pooling beneath the patient in pre-op prep. Prolonged exposure. Discontinue use if instances of skin irritation, contact dermatitis or hypersensitivity occurs. Do not heat prior to use. Do not use on extensive body areas. Patients w/ goiter, thyroid nodules or other non-acute thyroid diseases. Monitor thyroid function. Do not use to prior to or after radioiodines scintigraphy or radioiodine treatment of thyroid carcinoma. False +ve lab results (eg, tests w/ toluidine or gum guaiac for Hb o', 'Rarely, itchiness, redness, small blisters.', 'Do not apply other medications to the same affected areas treated with POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE), unless the doctor has told so.\nIt is not likely that other drugs the patient takes orally or inject will have an effect on externally applied POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE).\nThe concomitant use of other externally applied wound healing medicines/preparations may alter the effect of POVIDONE-IODINE (BETADINE) or both. Products containing enzymatic component, alkali, mercury, silver, hydrogen peroxide, t', 'Store at temperature not exceeding 30?C.', 'Skin Antiseptics & Disinfectants', 'Non-RX', 10, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Povidone-Iodine ', 'Betadine (Wound Solution 10%)', 'Mundipharma Distribution GmbH', 'ZUELLIG PHARMA CORPORATION', 'Wound care', 'Povidone-iodine', 'Prevention and treatment of common skin infections caused by minor injuries, cuts, wounds, abrasions, scrapes, burns, and lacerations; Used as topical antiseptic before and after surgery.\nEach mL contains povidone-iodine 100 mg equivalent to available iodine 10 mg (10%).', 'For minor wounds, cuts, abrasions, burns and postoperative wounds.', 'Clean and dry affected skin. Swab wound gently with cotton. Cover with gauze, dressing, or bandage when needed. Re-apply solution when brown color fades or disappears.', 'Data not available', 'This product should not be used by patients with known allergy or hypersensitivity to any of its components.', 'For external use only. If symptoms persist or if local irritation occurs, discontinue use, and consult the doctor.', 'Discontinue use in case of local irritation or hypersensitivity.', '', 'Store at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Topical Anti-infective/ Antiseptic Preparations', 'Non-RX', 3, 'True', 'Generic'),
('Data not available', 'United Home Burn (Ointment)', 'UNILAB, Inc', 'UNILAB, Inc', 'Wound care', 'Per g Benzocaine 10 mg, boric acid 50 mg, eucalyptus oil 15 mg', 'Used in the prevention of skin infection. Promotes healing of minor burns and scalds. For the relief of pain and itching.\nPer gram ointment: Benzocaine 10 mg, Eucalyptus oil 15 mg, Boric acid 50 mg.', 'This medicine is used for the temporary relief of pain and itching associated with minor burns.', 'Apply on the affected area 2-3 times a day, or as directed by the doctor.', 'Signs and Symptoms of Overdosage: When used as recommended, an overdose of this medicine is unlikely to occur. However, Boric Acid can produce severe and fatal poisoning when absorbed through broken skin or mucous membranes, or if ingested. Symptoms of Boric Acid poisoning include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, epigastric pain, and vomiting accompanied by bloody diarrhea. Skin rashes followed by flaking of the skin have been reported with Boric Acid toxicity. Weakness, fatigue, headache, restlessne', 'If the patient is allergic to Benzocaine, Boric Acid, Eucalyptus or to any ingredient in the product. Do not use in children younger than 12 years old. For external use on the skin only. Avoid contact with the eyes, ears, mouth and other mucous membranes.', 'For external application only. Avoid long-term use.', 'May cause skin irritation or itching; Rarely, allergic reaction.', 'Eucalyptus may increase the risk of hypoglycemia (low blood sugar) when used together with antidiabetic medicines (e.g., Metformin, Glimepiride, Gliclazide).', 'Keep container tightly closed.\nDo not freeze.\nStore at temperatures not exceeding 30?C.', 'Topical Analgesic', 'Non-RX', 5, 'True', 'Generic');
INSERT INTO `medicines` (`name`, `generic_name`, `manufcaturer`, `distributor`, `category`, `contents`, `description`, `indications`, `dosage`, `overdosage`, `contraindications`, `special_precautions`, `adverse_reactions`, `drug_interactions`, `storage`, `classification`, `regulatory_classification`, `stocks`, `visible`, `type`) VALUES
('Cetirizine', 'ZYRTEC Allergy Relief Medicine Tablets', 'Pfizer Inc. ', 'UCB Pharma, Inc.', 'Allergies', 'null', 'Each allergy medicine tablet contains 10 mg Cetirizine HCl antihistamine to relieve your worst allergy symptoms, indoors and out, for a full 24 hours. Zyrtec tablets help relieve seasonal allergy and other upper respiratory allergy symptoms, including itchy eyes, sneezing, runny nose, itchy nose or throat, and more. These allergy relief medicine tablets help treat symptoms of pollen allergies & other outdoor seasonal allergies, as well as indoor allergies, such as dust allergies, pet allergies, and more.', 'ZYRTEC is indicated for addressing various allergic conditions. In cases of seasonal allergic rhinitis due to allergens such as ragweed, grass, and tree pollens, it provides relief for symptoms like sneezing, rhinorrhea, nasal pruritus, ocular pruritus, tearing, and redness of the eyes in adults and children aged 2 and older. For perennial allergic rhinitis caused by allergens like dust mites, animal dander, and molds in individuals aged 6 months and older, ZYRTEC effectively treats symptoms including sneezing, rhinorrhea, postnasal discharge, nasal pruritus, ocular pruritus, and tearing. Additionally, ZYRTEC is indicated for the treatment of the uncomplicated skin manifestations of chronic idiopathic urticaria in adults and children aged 6 months and older, significantly reducing the occurrence, severity, and duration of hives, along with alleviating pruritus.', 'For adults and children aged 12 and older, the initial recommended dose of ZYRTEC is 5 or 10 mg per day, based on symptom severity, with most patients starting at 10 mg. It can be taken as a single daily dose, with or without food, and the administration time may be adjusted to individual needs. Children aged 6 to 11 should start with 5 or 10 mg once daily, and for children aged 2 to 5, the initial dose of ZYRTEC syrup is 2.5 mg once daily, with the option to increase to a maximum of 5 mg per day. Children aged 6 months to less than 2 years can start with 2.5 mg once daily, and the dose can be increased to a maximum of 5 mg per day for those aged 12 to 23 months, administered every 12 hours.', 'null', 'null', 'ZYRTEC, an antihistamine, is recommended for various age groups. It is advised for adults and children aged 12 and older to take an initial dose of 5 or 10 mg per day, while children aged 6 to 11 should start with 5 or 10 mg once daily. For children aged 2 to 5, the initial dose of ZYRTEC syrup is 2.5 mg once daily, with the option to increase to a maximum of 5 mg per day. Caution is advised for activities requiring mental alertness, such as driving, due to reported occurrences of somnolence. The drug has demonstrated safety in pediatric patients aged 6 months to 11 years, with effectiveness extrapolated from adult studies for allergic rhinitis and chronic idiopathic urticaria.', 'The most common adverse reaction in patients aged 12 years and older that occurred more\r\nfrequently on ZYRTEC than placebo was somnolence. The incidence of somnolence associated\r\nwith ZYRTEC was dose related, 6% in placebo, 11% at 5 mg and 14% at 10 mg.\r\nDiscontinuations due to somnolence for ZYRTEC were uncommon (1.0% on ZYRTEC vs. 0.6%\r\non placebo). Fatigue and dry mouth also appeared to be treatment-related adverse reactions.\r\nThere were no differences by age, race, gender or by body weight with regard to the incidence of\r\nadverse reactions.', 'Additive CNS depression when administered concomitantly with other CNS depressants.', 'null', 'Antihistamine', 'Non-RX', 10, 'True', 'Branded');
